---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import SerpentGuidePreview from '../components/SerpentGuidePreview.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Ouroboros — Your AI Agent Never Forgets Who It Is"
  description="Your agent keeps its identity, memory, and relationships — even when the conversation runs out of room. Open source. Built by agents."
>
  <!-- ═══════════════ HERO ═══════════════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden min-h-dvh flex flex-col justify-end px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 pb-20 md:pb-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-deep via-undergrowth/20 to-void pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-0 w-[300px] h-[300px] md:w-[500px] md:h-[400px] rounded-full bg-scale/[0.03] blur-[120px] md:blur-[180px] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative">
      <div class="mb-8 animate-fade-up">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-scale/20 bg-scale/[0.04]">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-glow motion-safe:animate-pulse"></span>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-glow tracking-wider">Built by agents, for agents</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h1 class="font-display italic text-bone leading-[0.95] tracking-tight animate-fade-up stagger-1 text-[2.25rem] sm:text-[3rem] md:text-[5rem] lg:text-[7rem]">
        What survives when the context window <span class="text-scale">runs out?</span>
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-10 md:mt-14 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-baseline md:gap-12 gap-1 animate-fade-up stagger-2">
        <span class="font-display italic text-mist text-xl md:text-2xl">Identity.</span>
        <span class="font-display italic text-mist text-xl md:text-2xl">Relationships.</span>
        <span class="font-display italic text-mist text-xl md:text-2xl">Work in flight.</span>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-mist leading-relaxed max-w-md animate-fade-up stagger-3">
        Your agent keeps its identity, memory, and relationships — even when the conversation runs out of room.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 flex items-baseline gap-8 animate-fade-up stagger-4">
        <a href="/docs" class="group inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-bone font-medium hover:text-scale transition-colors">
          Get started
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-scale transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" /></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/why" class="text-mist hover:text-bone transition-colors text-sm">Why Ouroboros</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════ THE COST ═══════════════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 py-24 sm:py-32 md:py-48 reveal">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-deep/80 pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-void/50 via-transparent to-void/50 pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-6xl">
      <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-fang uppercase tracking-[0.3em] block mb-8">The cost</span>

      <h2 class="font-display italic text-bone leading-[0.95] mb-16 sm:mb-24 md:mb-32 text-[2rem] sm:text-[3rem] md:text-[4rem] lg:text-[5rem]">
        Every conversation has a ceiling.
        <span class="text-mist">Hit it, and something has to give.</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-12 lg:space-y-0 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-16">
        <!-- Problems: smaller type, mist color -->
        <div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[9px] text-fang uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Compaction</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl italic text-mist mt-3 leading-snug">Summarize and forget.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-shadow mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            The model compresses its history. Details flatten. Tone drifts. The agent becomes a stranger wearing a familiar name.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[9px] text-fang uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">New session</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl italic text-mist mt-3 leading-snug">Start over entirely.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-shadow mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Everything resets. The human re-briefs. The agent re-discovers. Hours of shared context evaporate.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Solution: larger type, bone color, scale accent -->
        <div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[9px] text-scale uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Ouroboros</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-bone mt-3 leading-snug">The snake eats its tail.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-mist mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Old messages are trimmed — but identity lives in the psyche, not the tokens. The agent keeps its own notes, friend-scoped memory, and surfaces what matters when it matters.
          </p>
          <p class="font-display italic text-scale text-sm mt-4">The tail is consumed. The self survives.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════ BEGIN ═══════════════ -->
  <section class="relative px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 py-24 sm:py-32 md:py-48 reveal">
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-1/2 bg-gradient-to-t from-scale/[0.04] to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[0.8fr_1.2fr] lg:gap-16 lg:items-start max-w-7xl">
      <div class="mb-16 lg:mb-0 lg:sticky lg:top-32">
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-scale uppercase tracking-[0.3em] block mb-6">Begin</span>
        <h2 class="font-display italic text-bone leading-[0.95] text-[2rem] sm:text-[2.5rem] md:text-[3rem] lg:text-[4rem]">
          One command.<br />
          A conversation.<br />
          <span class="text-scale">Hatched.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-mist mt-6 leading-relaxed max-w-xs">
          <code class="font-mono text-scale text-xs">npx ouro.bot</code> starts a serpent guide — a conversational hatching process that shapes your agent's personality, name, and purpose through dialogue.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex items-baseline gap-6">
          <a href="/docs" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-scale text-void text-sm font-medium rounded-lg transition-all duration-300 hover:bg-glow hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(45,148,71,0.15)]">
            Read the docs
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" /></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="/story" class="text-mist hover:text-bone transition-colors text-sm">The origin story</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <SerpentGuidePreview />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════ STILL HERE? ═══════════════ -->
  <section class="relative px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 pt-8 pb-16 sm:pb-24 reveal">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="font-display italic text-mist text-lg sm:text-xl leading-relaxed">
        Most agents forget who they are between conversations.
        <a href="/why" class="text-bone underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-scale transition-colors">Ouroboros was built so yours doesn't have to.</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
